caption.text:
#DIRGAHAYU INDONESIA KU YANG KE-72!

Semangat perjuangan itu tetap di dalam asa, menembus tulang-tulang. Untuk setiap pahlawan-pahlawan perjuangan, ku pastikan perjuangan kalian tidak sia-sia. Karena sampai sekarang bangsa ini masi berjuang: melawan kebodohan, melawan kemiskinan, melawan paham-paham palsu baik dan buruk, melawan tikus-tikus disetiap institusi negara, melawan setiap isu-isu pemecah, ya sampai sekarang kami masih berjuang untuk melawan setiap pola pikir yang salah!

Generasi ini masih terus mengemban tugas untuk membawa Indonesia ke kemerdekaan sesungguhnya, yaitu dimana keadilan yang nyata dan merata serta kesejahteraan sosial untuk setiap manusianya.

Dimanapun kau hari-hari ini memilih untuk berkontribusi bagi bangsa ini, besar ataupun kecil, itu sungguh berarti! Itu berdampak!

Maka dari itu, jangan menyerah wahai Putra Putri kebanggaan Bangsa! Bertahan! 
Berjuang terus dalam menuntaskan tugas! 
#MERDEKA !!!!

A pioneer. A heroine. An inspiration.

For me, more than just a national figure, I considered R.A. Kartini as one of Indonesia's prominent human right activists since she had set the bar for us, fellow women, on how to overcome discrimination and confinement.

113 years after she died, her spirit towards equality remains a breath of hope for us, Putri-putri Indonesia.

Today we celebrate your life, Ma'am. We took the baton you've passed from generation to generation. The baton of willingness to flourish women's emancipation. Not only to get better education but also the courage to take the leading role for enlightening and civilizing society.

#HappyKartiniDay #SelamatHariKartini #Kartini #RAKartini #21April #HumanRights #Inspiration #PerempuanIndonesia

caption.text:
Heart beating fast as we wait patiently to see who'll be in charge as DKI 1 for next period. 
It's been brutal, not only for the candidates but also for us, Jakartans. For the past 6 months, I've never seen such nerve-racking atmosphere: friendship torn apart, family intensely argued, colleagues left SNS, neighbours bad mouthing each other.

We've been bombarded by political dramas through media-plays, hoax news, hatred opinions,and unending debate panels. We're exhausted yet we STILL cast our vote for today. Jakartans, once again, proved themselves strong, persevering and a firm believer that the best is yet to come.

So now, I hope nothing but the best for my beloved city. May the candidate with the best competencies and utmost sincerity to serve the people got elected. May all the votes reflect the face of this city: those hard working and kind hearted human beings who respect diversity. 
#HopeForJakarta #DKI #Pilkada2017 #PilkadaJakarta
